quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  88,22,"You are not over them a controller."
  88,23,"However, he who turns away and disbelieves"
  88,24,"Then Allāh will punish him with the greatest punishment."
  89,19,"And you consume inheritance, devouring [it] altogether,{1}",footnotes:1:[Not caring whether it is lawful or unlawful.]
  89,20,"And you love wealth with immense love."
  89,21,"No! When the earth has been leveled - pounded and crushed"
  90,13,"It is the freeing of a slave"
  90,14,"Or feeding on a day of severe hunger"
  90,15,"An orphan of near relationship"
  91,10,"And he has failed who instills it [with corruption]."
  91,11,"Thamūd denied [their prophet] by reason of their transgression,"
  91,12,"When the most wretched of them was sent forth.{1}",footnotes:1:[To hamstring the she-camel which had been sent by Allāh as a sign to them.]
  92,7,"We will ease him toward ease."
  92,8,"But as for he who withholds and considers himself free of need"
  92,9,"And denies the best [reward],"
  93,4,"And the Hereafter is better for you than the first [life]."
  93,5,"And your Lord is going to give you, and you will be satisfied."
  93,6,"Did He not find you an orphan and give [you] refuge?"
  94,1,"Did We not expand for you, [O Muḥammad], your breast?{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., enlighten, assure and gladden your heart with guidance.]
  94,2,"And We removed from you your burden{1}",footnotes:1:[By forgiving any errors which you may have committed previously or might commit consequently. "Burden" can also refer to the anxiety experienced by the Prophet (ﷺ) at the beginning of his mission.]
  94,3,"Which had weighed upon your back"